<statement><div><p> Given the complex numbers z = <m>{1-\mathrm{i}}</m> and w = <m>{6}</m>, evaluate and write in the form <m>a+bi</m>, where <m>a</m> and <m>b</m> are real numbers. </p>
<p><em> Note: To write the complex number <m>{\mathrm{i}}</m> type  <c>i</c>, and 
<m>\sqrt{a}</m> type <c>sqrt(a)</c></em></p>
<p><alert>(i)</alert> <m>z\times w = </m>  <fillin characters="9" name="ans3"/> </p>
<p><alert>(ii)</alert><m> \displaystyle \frac{z}{w} = </m> <fillin characters="9" name="ans4"/> </p></div></statement>
<solution><div><h3>Worked Solution</h3>
<p>Given complex numbers:  <m>z={1-\mathrm{i}}</m> and  <m>w={6}</m>.</p>

<br/><alert>(i)</alert><alert> <m> z \times w </m></alert>
<p>   <m> z \times w = ({1-\mathrm{i}}) \times ({6}) </m></p>
  <p> Using FOIL method for multiplication: <m>(a+b)×(c+d)=ac+ad+bc+bd</m></p>
 <p>  <m>z \times w = {6-6 \mathrm{i}}</m></p>
   <p>So, <m> z \times w </m> in the form <m> a + bi </m> is <m> {6-6 \mathrm{i}} </m>.</p>

<br/><alert>(ii)</alert><alert> <m> \displaystyle \frac{z}{w}</m></alert>
<p>To find the division of complex numbers <m>\displaystyle  \frac{z}{w} </m> where <m> z = {1-\mathrm{i}} </m> and <m> w = {6} </m>, you can follow these steps:</p>
<p>1. Express <m> z </m> and <m> w </m> in the form <m> a + bi </m>, where <m> a </m> is the real part and <m> b </m> is the imaginary part of the complex number.</p>

<p>2. Use the formula for division of complex numbers: <m> \displaystyle  \frac{z}{w} = \frac{a + bi}{c + di} = \frac{(a + bi)(c - di)}{c^2 + d^2}, w \neq 0 </m>, where <m> c </m> and <m> d </m> are the real and imaginary parts of (<m> w </m>).</p>

<p>Applying this to our problem:</p>

<p>Given <m> z = {1-\mathrm{i}} </m> and <m> w = {6}</m>, let's calculate <m> \displaystyle \frac{z}{w} </m>:</p>

<p>Step 1: Express <m> z </m> and <m> w </m> in the form <m> a + bi </m>:<br/>
<m>  \displaystyle z = {1-\mathrm{i}} </m> (So, <m> a = {1} </m> and <m> b = {-1} </m>)<br/>
<m>  \displaystyle w ={6} </m> (So, <m> c = {6} </m> and <m> d = {0} </m>)</p>

<p>Step 2: Use the division formula:<br/>
<m> \displaystyle \frac{z}{w} = \frac{({1-\mathrm{i}})({6})}{({6})^2 + ({0})^2} </m></p>

<p>Now, perform the multiplication in the numerator:<br/>
<m> \displaystyle \frac{z}{w} = \frac{{6 \left(1-\mathrm{i}\right)}}{{36}+ {0}} \\
  \displaystyle\frac{z}{w} ={\frac{1}{6}}{-}{\frac{1}{6}}{\mathrm{i}} 
</m></p></div></solution>
<answer><p><m>6-6 \mathrm{i}</m></p></answer>
<answer><p><m>\frac{1}{6}-\frac{\mathrm{i}}{6}</m></p></answer>
